&lt;p&gt;Gigs is on a mission to build the world&#39;s largest and first truly global telecom carrier. We are making the telecom stack fully and easily programmable, the way modern fintechs did for payments. Nobody else has abstracted the messy telecom legacy at this scale, which is one reason brands like Nubank, PicPay, Revolut, Cash App and others are already building on our platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our engineering org is distributed across Berlin, Amsterdam, London, and New York. São Paulo is our newest hub, in a business critical market, and you will be its founding leader.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your first mandate is continuity: you inherit our Network Integrations Americas team, today distributed across Europe, and bring its center of gravity to São Paulo without losing momentum on live, launch-critical work. You will line-manage the team, run a deliberate handover from the current European engineers, and build the local cohort that becomes the team&#39;s core.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From there, you partner with the VP of Engineering and other leaders to shape what the hub becomes: which domains land in São Paulo next, and how the site grows.&lt;/p&gt;
